15.text: the imminent danger which threatened them

247.text: and old Ferrier upon one of the horses

quotes.text: "Maybe you don't know us,"
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "This here is the son of Elder Drebber, and I'm Joseph Stangerson, who travelled with you in the desert when the Lord stretched out His hand and gathered you into the true fold."
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "As He will all the nations in His own good time,"
quotes.speaker: His

quotes.text: "He grindeth slowly but exceeding small."
quotes.speaker: His

quotes.text: "We have come,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "at the advice of our fathers to solicit the hand of your daughter for whichever of us may seem good to you and to her. As I have but four wives and Brother Drebber here has seven, it appears to me that my claim is the stronger one."
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Nay, nay, Brother Stangerson,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "the question is not how many wives we have, but how many we can keep. My father has now given over his mills to me, and I am the richer man."
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "But my prospects are better,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "When the Lord removes my father, I shall have his tanning yard and his leather factory. Then I am your elder, and am higher in the Church."
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "It will be for the maiden to decide,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "We will leave it all to her decision."
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Look here,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "when my daughter summons you, you can come, but until then I don't want to see your faces again."
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "There are two ways out of the room,"
quotes.speaker: Ferrier

quotes.text: "there is the door, and there is the window. Which do you care to use?"
quotes.speaker: Ferrier

quotes.text: "Let me know when you have settled which it is to be,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "You shall smart for this!"
quotes.speaker: Stangerson

quotes.text: "You have defied the Prophet and the Council of Four. You shall rue it to the end of your days."
quotes.speaker: Stangerson

quotes.text: "The hand of the Lord shall be heavy upon you,"
quotes.speaker: Stangerson

quotes.text: "He will arise and smite you!"
quotes.speaker: Ferrier

quotes.text: "Then I'll start the smiting,"
quotes.speaker: Ferrier

quotes.text: "The young canting rascals!"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "I would sooner see you in your grave, my girl, than the wife of either of them."
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "And so should I, father,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "but Jefferson will soon be here."
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "Yes. It will not be long before he comes. The sooner the better, for we do not know what their next move may be."
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Twenty-nine days are given you for amendment, and then--"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Good God!"
quotes.speaker: John Ferrier

quotes.text: "How you scared me! Whatever made you come in like that."
quotes.speaker: John Ferrier

quotes.text: "Give me food,"
quotes.speaker: John Ferrier

quotes.text: "I have had no time for bite or sup for eight-and-forty hours."
quotes.speaker: John Ferrier

quotes.text: "Does Lucy bear up well?"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Yes. She does not know the danger,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "That is well. The house is watched on every side. That is why I crawled my way up to it. They may be darned sharp, but they're not quite sharp enough to catch a Washoe hunter."
quotes.speaker: John Ferrier

quotes.text: "You're a man to be proud of,"
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "There are not many who would come to share our danger and our troubles."
quotes.speaker: Lucy

quotes.text: "You've hit it there, pard,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "I have a respect for you, but if you were alone in this business I'd think twice before I put my head into such a hornet's nest. It's Lucy that brings me here, and before harm comes on her I guess there will be one less o' the Hope family in Utah."
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "What are we to do?"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "To-morrow is your last day, and unless you act to-night you are lost. I have a mule and two horses waiting in the Eagle Ravine. How much money have you?"
quotes.speaker: Lucy

quotes.text: "Two thousand dollars in gold, and five in notes."
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "That will do. I have as much more to add to it. We must push for Carson City through the mountains. You had best wake Lucy. It is as well that the servants do not sleep in the house."
quotes.speaker: Lucy

quotes.text: "We must make our start at once,"
quotes.speaker: Jefferson Hope

quotes.text: "The front and back entrances are watched, but with caution we may get away through the side window and across the fields. Once on the road we are only two miles from the Ravine where the horses are waiting. By daybreak we should be half-way through the mountains."
quotes.speaker: Ferrier

quotes.text: "What if we are stopped,"
quotes.speaker: Ferrier

quotes.text: "If they are too many for us we shall take two or three of them with us,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "To-morrow at midnight,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "When the Whip-poor-Will calls three times."
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "It is well,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Shall I tell Brother Drebber?"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Pass it on to him, and from him to the others. Nine to seven!"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Seven to five!"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Hurry on! hurry on!"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "We are through the line of sentinels. Everything depends on speed. Hurry on!"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Who goes there?"
quotes.speaker: him

quotes.text: "Travellers for Nevada,"
quotes.speaker: Jefferson Hope

quotes.text: "By whose permission?"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "The Holy Four,"
quotes.speaker: Ferrier

quotes.text: "Nine from seven,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Seven from five,"
quotes.speaker: Jefferson Hope

quotes.text: "Pass, and the Lord go with you,"
quotes.speaker: his
